headline.main: RABAUL IS HARD HIT; Allies Splash 33 Tons of Bombs on Goal of Pacific Drive ENEMY AIR LOSSES AT 123 Only 25 U. S. Planes Are Shot Down, With 10 Pilots Saved as Fliers Pace Offensive ALLIED OFFENSIVE IN PACIFIC PRESSED U.S. RETAINS INITIATIVE IN THE SOLOMONS

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN AUSTRALIA, Saturday, July 3 -- Australian jungle fighters from the interior have joined American troops at Nassau Bay on the New Guinea coast in a move threatening the southern approaches to the Japanese base at Salamaua, a communique revealed today, and the ground situation is unchanged on New Georgia Island in the central Solomons where United States troops are headed for the Munda base.
